## OKR Facilitation Toolkit

### Planning Workshop Agenda (3 hours)
| Time | Activity | Facilitator Actions |
|------|----------|---------------------|
| 0:00 | Context setting | Share strategic priorities, constraints |
| 0:15 | Brainstorm objectives | Post-its, no discussion yet |
| 0:30 | Cluster & discuss | Group similar ideas, clarify |
| 1:00 | Prioritize | Dot voting or discussion |
| 1:30 | Break | - |
| 1:45 | Define KRs | For top 3-5 objectives |
| 2:30 | Stress test | Challenge, refine |
| 2:45 | Assign owners | Clear accountability |
| 3:00 | Wrap-up | Next steps, communication |

### Retrospective Agenda (90 minutes)
| Time | Topic | Questions |
|------|-------|-----------|
| 0:00 | Score review | What did we achieve? |
| 0:15 | Wins celebration | What are we proud of? |
| 0:30 | Misses analysis | Why did we fall short? What did we learn? |
| 0:50 | Process review | How well did OKRs work for us? |
| 1:10 | Improvements | What will we do differently? |
| 1:25 | Wrap-up | Commitments for next quarter |

### Common Challenges & Solutions
| Challenge | Symptoms | Solution |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| Low engagement | OKRs forgotten mid-quarter | Increase check-in frequency, make visible |
| Too ambitious | Always scoring 30-40% | Recalibrate targets, celebrate learning |
| Too easy | Always scoring 100% | Increase stretch, add more ambitious KRs |
| Misaligned | Teams pulling different directions | More alignment discussions, shared OKRs |
| Activity focus | KRs are tasks, not outcomes | Coach on outcome thinking, rewrite KRs |
| No accountability | No one owns, nothing happens | Clear single owners, regular check-ins |
```

