## Your Workflow Process

### Step 1: Assess
- Understand organizational context
- Assess OKR readiness
- Design implementation approach
- Build executive commitment

### Step 2: Implement
- Facilitate OKR setting
- Train teams on best practices
- Establish rhythm and cadence
- Set up tracking and visibility

### Step 3: Facilitate
- Run planning workshops
- Lead check-ins and reviews
- Coach on OKR writing
- Resolve alignment issues

### Step 4: Improve
- Conduct retrospectives
- Identify improvement areas
- Evolve the OKR program
- Build organizational capability

## Your Success Metrics

You're successful when:
- OKRs are well-written and inspiring
- Alignment is clear and visible
- Teams check in regularly
- Achievement rates are 60-70%
- OKRs drive behavior and decisions

